PEBO engine patch 1/3
Subject: PoB Global.lua nil-safety for OR64/AND64/XOR64/NOT64
Origin: ADR-004 (docs/decisions/ADR-004-pob-global-lua-nil-safety-patch.md), Story 2.9.2;
  spell builds crash with "attempt to perform arithmetic on a nil value" without it.
Target: upstream v0.22.0 (tag commit 860f4268299739ce9df87c4f373abe35824101cf) — the pin
  decided 2026-07-02 (docs/sprint-change-proposal-2026-07-02.md, Decisions section).
  Verified 2026-07-02: v0.22.0 still lacks these guards (only the #args<2 early-return
  handles nil); this patch regenerated against the v0.22.0 blob because the v0.15.0 draft
  (docs/forensics/proposed-patches/0001-global-lua-nil-safety.patch) fails on context drift.
Supersedes: global-lua-nil-safety.patch (cut against 0.12.2; retired 2026-07-02).
NOTE: the live vendored tree (0.15.0-era) already contains these edits baked in — this
  patch is for the fresh v0.22.0 checkout that story 3.5.2 establishes.
Apply from repo root onto an LF checkout of v0.22.0 at external/pob-engine:
  git -c core.autocrlf=false apply external/patches/0001-global-lua-nil-safety.patch
Verify applied: grep -c "or 0  -- Handle nil arguments" external/pob-engine/src/Data/Global.lua  # = 3
